Package: edaphos
Title: Disruptive Algorithms for Digital Soil Mapping
Version: 3.7.0
Authors@R:
    person("Hugo", "Rodrigues", , "rodrigues.machado.hugo@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8070-8126"))
Description: A research-oriented R package that implements frontier
    algorithms for Digital Soil Mapping (DSM) beyond the current
    regression-tree state of the art. The package is organised around
    six research pillars, each confronting a specific methodological
    gap of the literature: (1) Causal AI with backdoor-adjusted effect
    estimation on pedogenetic Directed Acyclic Graphs; (2) Physics-
    Informed Machine Learning of the soil depth profile via a
    parametric pedogenetic Ordinary Differential Equation and a
    differentiable Neural Ordinary Differential Equation, including a
    covariate-conditioned hierarchical extension across pedons;
    (3) 4D Pedometry with a multi-layer stacked Convolutional Long
    Short-Term Memory network, sequence-to-sequence training,
    multi-step rollout forecasting, an optional physics-informed
    mass-balance loss and a stochastic Ensemble Kalman Filter for
    sequential assimilation of new in-situ observations; (4) Foundation Models via SimCLR-style
    contrastive pre-training on unlabelled raster covariate patches;
    (5) Autonomous Active Learning with a hybrid uncertainty +
    feature-space-diversity batch policy, logistical cost-aware
    extension, and Physics-Informed rejection gates; (6) Quantum ML
    with a pure-R state-vector simulator of the ZZFeatureMap
    encoding, a quantum kernel Gram matrix and a closed-form Kernel
    Ridge Regression wrapper. A synthesised Cerrado covariate-and-
    response cube is bundled so every vignette runs offline and
    reproducibly.
